name: Airlines
summary:
**American Airlines News**

American Airlines is making changes to improve the travel experience. The carrier is discontinuing international flights from Charlotte's airport (CLT) and implementing a new boarding procedure designed to reduce line-cutting at over 100 airports. Additionally, American Airlines is cracking down on "gate lice," passengers who stake out boarding spots early to avoid waiting in line. Despite these changes, the airline is also experimenting with a new boarding process that may be more convenient for passengers. name: Jay Bhattacharya
summary: Former President Donald Trump has nominated Dr. Jay Bhattacharya to be the director of the National Institutes of Health (NIH). Bhattacharya, a Stanford physician and economist, has been a vocal critic of COVID-19 mandates and lockdowns. His appointment has generated controversy, as some scientists have expressed concern about his views on the pandemic. However, Bhattacharya has defended his position, arguing that his focus on data and individual freedom is consistent with the NIH's mission. If confirmed by the Senate, Bhattacharya will oversee a vast network of biomedical research institutions dedicated to improving public health.
